---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Differentiation Rules" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-11/" backLabel="← Grade 11">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Differentiation Rules</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Product, quotient and chain rule</p>
	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Complex Derivatives</h2>
		<p>For products, quotients and compositions we need special rules.</p>
		<h3>🧪 Experiment</h3>
		<p>Observe f(x) = x·sin(x):</p>
	</section>
	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fn={(x) => x * Math.sin(x)} fnLabel="f(x) = x·sin(x)" xMin={-7} xMax={7} yMin={-5} yMax={7} />
	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 The Three Rules</h3>
		<ul><li>Product rule: (f·g)' = f'·g + f·g'</li><li>Quotient rule: (f/g)' = (f'·g − f·g') / g²</li><li>Chain rule: (f(g(x)))' = f'(g(x)) · g'(x)</li></ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
